<div id="review_10675012" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/10675012" />
    <a title="Jim" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/695116-jim"><img alt="Jim" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1340192527p2/695116.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/10675012?book_show_action=true">Dec 19, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jim" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jim" href="/user/show/695116-jim">Jim</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/695116-jim?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/695116-jim?shelf=3series">3series</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/695116-jim?shelf=1paper">1paper</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/695116-jim?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/695116-jim?shelf=2fiction">2fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/695116-jim?shelf=sword-sorcery">sword-sorcery</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer10675012" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5042657390469481849">I&apos;ve probably read this 4 or 5 times. It&apos;s fun, entertaining &amp; amusing. I liked this first trilogy better than the second (Tamuli) but both are good if you&apos;re looking for something quick, light &amp; entertaining.<br/><br/>Sparhawk is a great character, a battered knight, but his horse Faran is my favorite. It&apos;s nice to see a horse as a character. More authors should do this.</span>
  <span id="freeText5042657390469481849" style="display:none">I've probably read this 4 or 5 times. It's fun, entertaining &amp; amusing. I liked this first trilogy better than the second (Tamuli) but both are good if you're looking for something quick, light &amp; entertaining.<br /><br />Sparhawk is a great character, a battered knight, but his horse Faran is my favorite. It's nice to see a horse as a character. More authors should do this.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5042657390469481849" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


