              <span id="reviewTextContainer172606500" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9301489748134800867">Reread this book for what may be the sixth or seventh time. It&apos;s a day read, potato chip craving that somehow moves beyond.<br/><br/>This book has the elements I cherish most. It has plot, pacing, action, and character development. If you are a slow reader the book may lack urgency. <br/><br/>Sparhawk is a three-dimensional character, not the best but far from the worst. You get to know the first few characters in the starter and the plot presents equally appealing dual conflicts. <br/><br/>If you haven&apos;t read anything by Da</span>
  <span id="freeText9301489748134800867" style="display:none">Reread this book for what may be the sixth or seventh time. It's a day read, potato chip craving that somehow moves beyond.<br /><br />This book has the elements I cherish most. It has plot, pacing, action, and character development. If you are a slow reader the book may lack urgency. <br /><br />Sparhawk is a three-dimensional character, not the best but far from the worst. You get to know the first few characters in the starter and the plot presents equally appealing dual conflicts. <br /><br />If you haven't read anything by David Eddings, this is where to start.</span>
