<div id="review_2937392055" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2937392055" />
    <a title="Tom" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/92841880-tom"><img alt="Tom" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2937392055?book_show_action=true">Aug 14, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tom" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tom" href="/user/show/92841880-tom">Tom</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780246134486" href="/book/show/983173.The_Diamond_Throne">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2937392055" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7524743708202894652">This was my second time reading this after loving it as a teenager, and I was interested to see if it was actually as good as I remembered it. <br/><br/>It was. <br/><br/>The writing style is so easy to read, the characters are introduced and fleshed out with good pacing and the world is well explained without being overwhelming. Some of the characters are a bit fantasy-stereotyped, but that’s not a problem for me. The pacing is great, it never feels like it’s dragging, nor does it feel overwhelmed by action. <br/><br/>I’ll </span>
  <span id="freeText7524743708202894652" style="display:none">This was my second time reading this after loving it as a teenager, and I was interested to see if it was actually as good as I remembered it. <br /><br />It was. <br /><br />The writing style is so easy to read, the characters are introduced and fleshed out with good pacing and the world is well explained without being overwhelming. Some of the characters are a bit fantasy-stereotyped, but that’s not a problem for me. The pacing is great, it never feels like it’s dragging, nor does it feel overwhelmed by action. <br /><br />I’ll be re-reading the rest of the trilogy, and recommend any high fantasy fan to give it a try. <br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="7524743708202894652" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


